250 g Ground Chicken
2 unit(s) Artisan Bun
⅓ cup Panko Breadcrumbs
170 g Coleslaw Cabbage Mix
1 unit(s) Mini Cucumber
7 g Cilantro
1 unit(s) Lime
1 unit(s) Garlic, cloves
4 tbsp Mango Chutney
2 tbsp Mayonnaise
2 tbsp Jerk Sauce
1 tbsp Unsalted Butter*
2 tbsp Oil*
0.38 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Peel, then mince or grate garlic.
Add chicken, garlic, panko, 1 1/2 tbsp (3 tbsp) jerk sauce and 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) salt to a medium bowl. Season with pepper, then combine.
Form chicken mixture into two 5-inch-wide patties (4 patties for 4 ppl). (NOTE: Your mixture may look wet; this is normal. In step 2, you can carefully re-shape patties when cooking.)

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then chicken. Cook, breaking up chicken into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.** (TIP: Reduce heat to medium if patties are browning too quickly.)

Meanwhile, halve cucumber lengthwise, then cut into 1/4-inch half-moons.
Zest, then juice lime.
Roughly chop cilantro.

Meanwhile, combine mayo and 3 tbsp (6 tbsp) mango chutney in a small bowl. Season with salt and pepper.

Add remaining mango chutney, remaining jerk sauce, 2 tsp (4 tsp) lime juice, 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) lime zest and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil to a large bowl, then whisk to combine. Season with salt and pepper.
Add cabbage coleslaw mix, cucumber and cilantro to the bowl with dressing. Toss to combine.

Halve buns, then spread 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) softened butter on the cut side of each half.
Arrange on an unlined baking sheet, cut-side up.
Broil in the top of the oven until golden-brown, 1-2 min. (TIP: Keep an eye on them so they don't burn!)
Spread mango chutney mayo on buns. Stack patties and some of the coleslaw on bottom buns. Close with top buns.
Divide burgers and remaining coleslaw between plates.

If you've opted to get chicken, prep and cook it in the same way the recipe instructs you to prep and cook the turkey.